{
  "stem": "21139.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we had no playmates, except the few Jewish people that were still living there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But more and more left.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And at the end, there was just Siegie and I.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And because-- either they moved to Pforzheim or they immigrated to different parts of the world.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My sister was in Hamburg.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she was training there as some profession and I don't even recall anymore what it was.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I know she was training for something.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My brother Julius was in a town, Geislingen it was called, I remember, in training also for some profession.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I don't know what it was.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And as a matter of fact, in November of 1938, Kristallnacht, they took my brother Julius, who was 16 years old at the time, to Dachau.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[CRYING] [SIGHS] He-- he was there [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] about two months.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And they let him go under the condition that he leaves the country.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So my-- we had an uncle still living in Belgium, which is a brother of my mother.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he had a daughter living in Manchester, England.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So my parents got in touch with my uncle, who got in touch with his daughter in order to get papers for my brother to leave.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And he did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And [CRYING] soon after, my sister left for England.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And she did there domestic work.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "My cousin also provided the papers.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And she got a family in Manchester where my sister could go to work for them.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So this way, the two got out earlier.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I-- I could have gone to England [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] [CRYING] But I didn't want to leave my parents alone, so I stayed at home.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And my youngest brother Siegie, he left in '39.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "He was seven years old.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
